d belief is the engine of Halliday’s poetry.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 0aAmerican poetryy21st century. 7aPOETRY / General.2bisacsh  apoetry, poems, literature, contemporary, loss, losing, winning, victory, dreams, dreaming, goals, hope, inspiration, time, mortality, forgetting, memory, remembrance, legacy, confusion, fulfillment, meaning, purpose, family, romance, relationships, citizenship, national identity, engagement, activism, promise, possibility, fiction, creative writing, emotion, irony, voice, belief, earnestness, sincerity, commitment, devotion.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Press Complete eBook-Package 2018z978311068858040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226533629423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780226533629/original  a978-3-11-068858-0  University of Chicago Press Complete eBook-Package 2018b2018  aGBV-deGruyter-alles